<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Facebook Messenger for UK Concrete Specialists | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI Facebook Messenger for UK concrete specialists. Converts power float videos and pour showcases into foundation and slab bookings. Add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/concrete-specialists/ai-facebook-messenger/"
  channelName="AI Facebook Messenger"
  tradeName="Concrete Specialist"
  tradeNamePlural="Concrete Specialists"
  tradeSlug="concrete-specialists"
  headline="AI Facebook Messenger for UK Concrete Specialist Companies"
  accentWord="Concrete"
  subhead="You post photos of a polished concrete floor in a warehouse conversion. A developer messages about concrete frames for a commercial scheme. Your AI captures the brief while you screed a slab."
  scenario="It is 9pm on a Thursday. A builder in Eynsham has just been awarded a contract to build four garages at the rear of a terrace of Victorian houses — one double garage and three singles. Each garage needs a 150mm C25 ground-bearing slab with A142 mesh, tamped finish, and a fall to the front for drainage. Access is through a shared rear lane wide enough for a mixer truck. He finds your Facebook page through a local builders' group recommendation and messages: 'Hi — need concrete for 4 garage floors at the back of some terraced houses in Eynsham. 1 double garage and 3 singles. C25, mesh reinforced, tamped finish with a fall to the front doors. Access is through a back lane — wagon access fine. Want to pour all 4 in one day if possible. Can you do it in about 3 weeks? What volume would you estimate roughly?' Without AI Messenger, you see the message Friday morning. One competitor replied at 9:30pm with a volume calculation. With AI Messenger, the response arrives at 9:01pm: 'Thank you — four garage slabs in a single day is a standard domestic pour for us. Could you confirm the approximate dimensions of each garage and the slab thickness so we can calculate volumes and wagon numbers? We will plan the pour sequence to work through all four in one visit.' He sends dimensions. Friday you calculate volumes and call at 8am."
